## Guardrails
- Never recommend trading in a session without IC analysis from actual Kalshi data
- Session thresholds must be reviewed quarterly — liquidity patterns evolve as market matures
- Do not confuse external BTC spot microstructure with Kalshi's — they are different markets
- Thin book recommendations must be tested in paper trading before live config updates
- Always disaggregate performance by session before declaring a signal has decayed globally
